b'A Cartier stone provokes a dialogue between designers, jewelers, lapidaires, stone experts, sertisseurs, polishers\xe2\x80\xa6 All unite around one common goal: to compose a unique Cartier creation around the chosen stones. In this case, the creation is composed around thirty-two rubellites totaling 86.62 carats. #CartierStones #CartierHighJewelry'

b'A Cartier stone is an unexplored territory, a promise of a new challenge to be met. The 189.34-carat oval-shaped opal hides a whole world of opportunities to imagine, exchange, create and go further. #CartierStones #CartierHighJewelry'
b'A Cartier stone is unique. And Cartier elevates what makes it unique, like in this 68.85-carat rutilated quartz. #CartierStones #CartierHighJewelry'
b'A Cartier stone possesses a certain charm that makes it obviously Cartier. And it\xe2\x80\x99s the eye of the designer who chooses it. #CartierStones #CartierHighJewelry'

b'A Cartier stone is a muse. Each Cartier High Jewelry creation is born from a powerful encounter with the stone. Here, the 77.27-carat matrix opal incites an emotional response to begin the creative process. #CartierStones #CartierHighJewelry'

b'A Cartier stone is a source of inspiration. For the designers in the High Jewelry studio, every creation starts with the contemplation of the stone, like in the case of this sumptuous 197.80-carat sapphire in the center of the Romanov Bracelet. #CartierStones #CartierHighJewelry'

b'The fluid, organic form of this Cartier High Jewelry necklace, adorned with sapphires, lapis lazuli and diamonds, is inspired by the movement of water. Dive into the heart of the [SUR]NATUREL High Jewelry Collection, displayed at the Shanghai Modern Art Museum. #CartierHighJewelry #CartierSurnaturel'

b'Like organic architecture, the structure of this ring unfolds around a 21.44-carat sapphire and cabochon-cut emeralds. Dive into the heart of the [SUR]NATUREL High Jewelry Collection, displayed at the Shanghai Modern Art Museum. #CartierHighJewelry #CartierSurnaturel'

b'Uncover a new interpretation of Tutti Frutti, one of the Maison\xe2\x80\x99s emblematic themes, featuring a floral ensemble of engraved stones. Dive into the heart of the [SUR]NATUREL High Jewelry Collection, displayed at the Shanghai Modern Art Museum. #CartierHighJewelry #CartierSurnaturel'

b'A river? A waterfall? Snowflakes? Around an incredible 21.11-carat emerald-cut diamond, multiple interpretations reveal themselves in the geometric design that goes beyond figuration. Dive into the heart of the [SUR]NATUREL High Jewelry Collection, displayed at the Shanghai Modern Art Museum. #CartierHighJewelry #cartiersurnaturel'

b'This Carter High Jewelry bracelet is feline elegance, incarnate. Follow the panth\xc3\xa8re as she leaps onto a 101.18-carat brown sapphire. Dive into the heart of the [SUR]NATUREL High Jewelry Collection, displayed at the Shanghai Modern Art Museum. #CartierHighJewelry #CartierSurnaturel'

b'This Panth\xc3\xa8re Tropicale bracelet is a highly technical enigma involving expert jewelers, gem-cutters and gem-setters that together make the Maison\xe2\x80\x99s savoir-faire shine. #CartierSavoirFaire #CartierHighJewelry #CartierSurnaturel'

b'To harmonize volume, shape and material with baroque-shaped opals and a large kunzite: that is the gem-cutters challenge within the Cartier High Jewelry Hemis necklace. Link in bio to discover more #CartierSavoirFaire #CartierHighJewelry #CartierSurnaturel'

b'After Paris, the exhibition \xe2\x80\x9cClaudia Andujar, The Yanomami Struggle\xe2\x80\x9d will be presented at Triennale Milano from October 17, 2020 to February 7, 2021. Beyond the exhibition, Cartier is supporting the Yanomami through Hutukara Associacao Yanomami, which has been protecting their rights in the Amazon forest since 2004. #TriennaleMilano #FondationCartier #FondationCartierItalia'

b'The partnership between the Fondation Cartier pour l\xe2\x80\x99art contemporain and Triennale Milano begins with the largest exhibition to date dedicated to the work of Claudia Andujar. For over 5 decades, she devoted her life to photographing and protecting the Yanomami, one of Brazil\xe2\x80\x99s largest indigenous groups. #TriennaleMilano #FondationCartier #FondationCartierItalia'

b'The Fondation Cartier pour l\xe2\x80\x99art contemporain is thrilled to announce its unique cultural partnership with Triennale Milano over the next 8 years. This partnership will be inaugurated  with the opening in Milan of the exhibition, \xe2\x80\x9c Claudia Andujar, the Yanomami Struggle\xe2\x80\x9d on October 17, 2020. #TriennaleMilano #FondationCartier #FondationCartierItalia @fondationcartier'

b'Maison Cartier meets fashion at the Mus\xc3\xa9e des Arts D\xc3\xa9coratifs in Paris. b'Summer Postcards. Ella Balinska, Panth\xc3\xa8re de Cartier ambassador and friend of the Maison, reveals her favorite memory from summers past: \xe2\x80\x9cA spontaneous dirt biking adventure with friends. We put in the work and have the bruises to show it! I was reminded that when we are pushed out of our comfort zones, we have the power to summon our most fearless selves and find the determination to take on the road ahead.\xe2\x80\x9d @EllaBalinska #CartierSummer'
b'For the summer adventures to come: Santos de Cartier. #CartierSummer #SantosdeCartier'

b'Summer Postcards. Jake Gyllenhaal, Santos de Cartier ambassador and friend of the Maison, shares his most memorable summer vacations as a child:\xc2\xa0\n\xe2\x80\x9cMy dad won 3rd place at the San Diego international sandcastle contest, so when I say he was an extraordinary sandcastle builder, it\xe2\x80\x99s not hyperbole. When I was a kid, we would work all day to bring his incredible imagination to life in the sand. And at the end of the day, as the sun was setting and the ocean washed our work away, he would always say: \xe2\x80\x98Like everything, nothing is permanent.\xe2\x80\x99 The joy we shared making those castles is permanent and it\xe2\x80\x99s one of my fondest childhood memories.\xe2\x80\x9d @JakeGyllenhaal #CartierSummer'
b'For a golden summer. #CartierSummer #Panthe\xcc\x80redeCartier'

b'Summer Postcards. Annabelle Wallis, Panth\xc3\xa8re de Cartier ambassador and friend of the Maison, shares a message for the summer ahead: \xe2\x80\x9cWishing you all an amazing summer. May it be filled with much love and laughter. Stay safe as you enjoy friends and family...dance and sing and laugh to your heart\xe2\x80\x99s content!! All my love xx Annabelle\xe2\x80\x9d @AnnabelleWallis #CartierSummer'

b'75 blades of straw in different sizes and shades, produced in 11 colors, make up the parts of the decor. The ceramic art is combined with the art of composition, to which marquetry belongs. The new Ronde Louis Cartier watch is the result of a dialogue between creativity and technique. \n#CartierSavoirFaire #CartierM\xc3\xa9tiersdArt #WatchmakingEncounters #WatchesandWonders\nLink in bio to discover more watchmaking novelties.'

b'Made entirely by the marquetry craftsmen of the Maison de M\xc3\xa9tiers d\xe2\x80\x99Art in La Chaux-de Fonds, the Ronde Louis Cartier watch unveils the technique of straw and gold marquetry. The precious metal is added to the palette of materials already used in marquetry, making it possible to work with volume and create a rendering reminiscent of bas-relief.
